def: A kind of lively dance, in 2-4 time; also, the music to thedance.
Having a shriveled, thin, withered face.
A count or earl who presided in the domestic court, and had thesuperintendence, of a royal household in Germany.
A small roof, covering, or shelter.
Of or pertaining to the open air; being under the open sky.[R.] N. Bacon.
The showing in court of a sufficient lawful reason why a partycharged or accused did that for which he is called to answer.
A form of air pump in which exhaustion is produced by a streamof mercury running down a narrow tube, in the manner of an aspirator;-- named from the inventor.
He who, or that which, accompanies. Lamb.
An instrument for triturating the stone in the bladder; alithotrite.
